data.description: Country roads take me HOME! This gorgeous 4 sided, brick, ranch home offers you a piece of paradise with 20 acres and two homes. The land is breathtaking and has so much potential with open pasture, hardwoods, pines, and a flowing stream. It is ideal for hunting, outdoor recreation, starting your own homestead, farming, and so much more. This home's craftsmanship is superb featuring hardwood floors, knotty pine paneling, and the most unique wooded ceilings found throughout the home. The kitchen is a chef's delight with custom cabinetry, brand new kitchen stainless steel appliances, huge handcrafted table island, along with lots storage and a pot rack to keep you organized and ready to prepare delicious meals. This spacious home offers endless possibilities with three additional rooms which could be used as an office, game room, weight room, or an extra bedroom. The possibilities are endless. There is ample storage throughout and the closets don't go unnoticed with either cedar or knotty pine walls. The two fireplaces located in the den and living room provides ambiance and warmth on those cooler days. But wait, there is so much more! A guest house is located on the property with 1 bedroom, 1 full bath, a bonus room, full kitchen, and living room equipped with its own electric meter and HVAC unit. The front or back screened in porch is the perfect place to relax and enjoy the exquisite landscape, sounds of nature, and a variety of wildlife. In addition to the homes, there is a 30 x 40 metal shop building with concrete floors and electricity and an outdoor storage building along with 2 deer stands on property will remain. High speed internet coming soon. An additional 56.81 acres can be purchase for $230K and adjoins this home and acreage. Located approx. 1 mile from the Tallapoosa River, 30-45 min. from Lake Wedowee, and about an hour away from Lake Martin. No need to wait. Call today to view this exquisite home.
